* Test a single pieace of code in isolation => something like single middleware (UNIT Test)
* Test how differnt pieces of code work together => Simulate a request flowing through some of the middlewares of to some route handler. 
* Test how multiple components work together => Something like how our auth service interact with mongoDB. Or how it interacts with event bus. 
* Test differnt services work together. Something like when orderservice emmit an event how does that flow to the ticketing service. 


Testing Goals. 

Test goal 1: Basic request handling. 

Testing goal 2: Some tests around models (unit tests).

Testing goal 3: Reciving and emmiting events.(incoming and outgoing events). 
We won't launch order service and ticketing service at the same time. But if we test the events of one service emmiting and reciving we are going at the 
same goal. 

How to execute these tests? 
Run all tests directly at the terminal. No docker no kubernetes. 

npm run test. 

Sometime in future we will be running some test where we need some kind of pirticular operating system , some very complex hard to run application. 

